		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have heard that there are several different pirate versions of super mario bros 2 that run on a cartridge instead of on the FDS. Does anyone know specificly which one runs on mapper 4 (MMC3)?  I have found one version that runs on mapper 4 but the title screen and some of the other graphics are corrupt.
<br />
<br />oh, BTW, i tried to use the search engine to look for help and it does not work, it can't even find my own thread (this one!) so I think something is broken.
<br />
<br />---disregard previous transmission---
<br />
<br />edit: I got the answer I need, so changing topics here to something else, 
<br />
<br />Does anyone know anything about the FFE mapper? I know that Far Front East made a RAM based cartridge copyer that had a special mapper that could simulate other mappers. How did this work? I think that a modified version of the FFE RAM unit might make a feasable and versatle flash / battery backed RAM cart for development or other things.

		

