	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You're confused, the thing *is* a "flash" (it's DRAM) cart. It is not an intelligent unit, it cannot tell what mapper a game has. It cannot simulate mappers. You must have ROMs modified to run on the SMC either that you modified yourself or obtained from Front Fareast which is just about impossible since this device was discontinued in 1992.
<br />
<br />If you want a piracy "development" device, you'll have to wait for Neoflash, they hinted at developing a NES one but I'll believe it when I see it.

		

		</td>
